<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="compliment-n">compliment <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'kɒmplɪmənt/    美 /'kɑːmplɪmənt/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>称赞；夸奖：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My deskmate admires my fluent English very much and I usually feel encouraged by his compliments.
我同桌非常欣赏我流利的英语，他的称赞也经常使我很受鼓舞。</p><footer>2013 湖北书面表达</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>When Richard said, “You are much more agreeable and prettier now,” Joan’s face turned red at the unexpected  <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (称赞).  （2014 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. compliment  </p></div>